# Julia testing

- Run tests via `jw` which keeps warm Julia sessions in tmux (one tab per package):
  - `jw start <path>` — start a Julia REPL tab with Revise + TestEnv
  - `jw run <path>` — run all tests
  - `jw run <path> <filter>` — run filtered tests (file:str, name:str, tag:sym, !tag:sym, or bare filename substring; combine with commas)
  - `jw output <path|name>` — capture recent output
  - `jw kill <path|name>` — kill tab (e.g. when Revise can't recompile)
  - `jw format [path]` — format Julia code (warm JuliaFormatter session)
- Always prefer `jw run` over `julia -e 'using Pkg; Pkg.test()'`.
- Revise auto-recompiles code, but changing structs may require restarting: `jw kill <name>` then re-run.
